@ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress = https://localhost:7311

### 1. [Produces] JSON action
GET {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/produces/json/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. [Produces] XML action
GET {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/produces/xml/1
Accept: application/xml

###

### 3. [Consumes] JSON only endpoint - valid JSON input
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/consumes/json-only
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "Name": "Mouse",
  "Category": "Accessories",
  "Price": 800,
  "InStock": true
}

###

### 4. [Consumes] XML only endpoint - valid XML input
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/consumes/xml-only
Content-Type: application/xml
Accept: application/xml

<ProductCreateRequest>
  <Name>Desk</Name>
  <Category>Furniture</Category>
  <Price>5500</Price>
  <InStock>true</InStock>
</ProductCreateRequest>

###

### 5. Controller-level JSON contract - valid JSON input
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/products
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "Name": "Monitor",
  "Category": "Electronics",
  "Price": 12000,
  "InStock": true
}

###

### 6. Controller-level default JSON response
GET {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/products/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Action-level override - XML response
GET {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/products/1/xml
Accept: application/xml

###

### 8. Action-level override - XML input and XML output
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/products/xml
Content-Type: application/xml
Accept: application/xml

<ProductCreateRequest>
  <Name>Printer</Name>
  <Category>Electronics</Category>
  <Price>15000</Price>
  <InStock>false</InStock>
</ProductCreateRequest>

###

### 9. Action-level override - Multipart form-data upload
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123
Accept: application/json

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello from upload sample
--boundary123--

###

### 10. Invalid input example - sending XML to JSON-only endpoint should return 415
POST {{ProducesConsumesDemo_HostAddress}}/api/consumes/json-only
Content-Type: application/xml
Accept: application/json

<ProductCreateRequest>
  <Name>Invalid Sample</Name>
  <Category>Test</Category>
  <Price>10</Price>
  <InStock>true</InStock>
</ProductCreateRequest>
